was established, per se, as such. I would say that 
if they had a planning commission established

03:01.491 --> 03:12.340
under the 61 charter, it would only be logical that 
a planning department to provide staff

03:01.491 --> 03:12.340
assistance to that commission would also have 
existed at that stage. It's kind of an inescapable

03:13.581 --> 03:15.663
conclusion. Now, it may have well been a city 
engineer or a planning inspector that was doing,

03:15.723 --> 03:25.892
or a department or building inspector doing the 
work, but I really don't know beyond that. If they

03:26.193 --> 03:33.322
had a planning staff persuade before that, it 
would have somewhat surprised me. Was there any

03:33.342 --> 03:36.186
relationship with citizen groups? Oh geez. A and 
B, what was the relationship between the planning

03:38.569 --> 03:46.980
department and the city council? There was 
tremendous relationships between citizens

03:50.932 --> 04:03.658
groups, extremely strong special interest 
groups in the community, neighborhood

03:50.932 --> 04:03.658
associations, historic associations, cultural 
societies, Almost any three people that got

04:03.841 --> 04:08.125
together had a common ax to grind. And part of it was 
the frustration of not having a city that was

04:08.485 --> 04:12.369
responsive. You couldn't get the staff to answer a 
question. You know, who put up the bicycle pathway

04:15.271 --> 04:18.014
signs? And half the city staff would refuse to 
answer for fear they would get somebody in

04:18.094 --> 04:22.338
trouble. And it turns out the guy wants to 
compliment the city on establishing a bicycle

04:22.358 --> 04:29.924
pathway, even though it may not be one of the most 
advanced designs. You know, the more, here are

04:30.185 --> 04:33.848
some lines and markings, and let it go with that. In

04:33.828 --> 04:45.399
many ways, the city staff reminisces very much 
about what it was like under the commissioner

04:33.828 --> 04:45.399
system, and you had to watch your step. There was no 
civil service protection. You made a mistake, you

04:47.101 --> 04:54.068
were canned immediately, and everything was 
political, and it was a very corrupt city. It was

04:54.628 --> 05:00.814
wide open gambling, mafioso, and you'd wind up in 
the bay if you weren't careful. And part of all of

05:01.807 --> 05:08.119
this was part of that 61 reform package to try to get 
some of that cleaned up. And some of the mansions

05:08.920 --> 05:13.309
those people lived in are still there, you know, 
the criminal elements. There's still a lot of

05:13.349 --> 05:15.553
gambling and prostitution. I shouldn't say it, 
but I'm absolutely convinced the police

05:15.593 --> 05:24.490
department, many elements of the police 
department was still on the take when I was there.

05:25.330 --> 05:30.877
Corruption in many aspects was pretty darn 
rampant, and it was kind of hard to get that image

05:25.330 --> 05:30.877
snapped out. The citizens absolutely

05:31.498 --> 05:36.905
were adamant. They were active. There was good 
community organization. We tended to support it

05:40.210 --> 05:47.119
because people that were active and citizens 
tended to support the kind of things that we

05:40.210 --> 05:47.119
thought needed to be done, too. And I'll be honest 
with you, a lot of them were just absolute pains in

05:47.740 --> 05:53.295
terms of the planning staff and department. They 
would pick us, you know, okay, you've got to put up

05:53.596 --> 05:57.868
with them for a while. We would put up with them for a 
while. They would call us and report things. We'd

06:02.668 --> 06:13.687
be sitting there trying to ramp up a grant 
application for $500,000, and they're screaming

06:02.668 --> 06:13.687
because somebody's putting up a chain-link fence 
in a historic district without any building

06:02.668 --> 06:13.687
permits. We'd have to drop that and try to get 
somebody out there to respond to it and red-tag it.

06:18.335 --> 06:21.942
and catch the guy that's doing business, you know, 
and so forth. And, you know, it's difficult

06:22.122 --> 06:24.987
working with people. They don't understand all 
the time why you don't respond immediately or to

06:25.047 --> 06:38.672
their satisfaction, particularly when there's a 
conflicting interest, you know, and you're kind

06:25.047 --> 06:38.672
of caught in the middle and there's a judge saying, 
well, we know why you're seeing that, but we don't

06:25.047 --> 06:38.672
have any legal basis or authority to act. So that's 
a problem. The planning staff's relationship

06:41.223 --> 06:45.008
with the city council was interesting. All city 
staffs would be drug into the city council

06:45.849 --> 06:54.101
chamber, particularly directors on occasion. 
