06:54.121 --> 07:01.372
more than anything else. If the city council had 
respect for the staff and thought they were

07:02.053 --> 07:07.140
competent, They would tend to listen and treat 
them as professionals. They also tended to treat

07:11.740 --> 07:17.386
most of the staff as being incompetent and not 
being professionals. The general feeling was, as

07:17.786 --> 07:27.496
left over from the commission days and the poor 
salaries, was that anybody that worked for

07:17.786 --> 07:27.496
Galveston obviously couldn't be that good. If 
they were any good, they would be gone within a

07:28.016 --> 07:36.925
short time, so there was no real point in doing much 
more than using them to your maximum within the

07:28.016 --> 07:36.925
short term. This is a common problem I think all 
cities have. If you're really going to get it, why

07:41.229 --> 07:43.494
are we working for us? And it permeates all levels 
of government. So that's a real problem. On the

07:51.209 --> 07:57.040
other hand, it's very obvious that they attract 
good attention and got things done and they notice

07:51.209 --> 07:57.040
things. But there was a lot of reasons that they 
should think many of the city staff were

07:57.712 --> 08:02.857
incompetent, because in fact they were. We had a 
city attorney, who I won't name now, who had come

08:04.279 --> 08:12.487
fresh out of law school and gotten a job as the third 
assistant city attorney, junior, bottom of the

08:04.279 --> 08:12.487
line. And he kind of stayed there. Well, of course, 
attorneys traditionally always get paid a little

08:13.628 --> 08:21.035
bit more, and that's the way they make connections 
within a community so they can go set up their own

08:13.628 --> 08:21.035
practice. You know, you win your spurs and win a few 
cases and get a reputation, and you go from there.

08:26.399 --> 08:39.682
